      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: configurable default agent ID (escape the 'main' prison) 🦞",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds support for overriding the hardcoded `\"main\"` fallback agent ID, so users with a single custom-named agent no longer get a ghost `agents/main/` default path/session identity when no `agents.list` is configured.\n\n## The Problem\n\n`DEFAULT_AGENT_ID` falls back to `\"main\"`. Some resolution paths run from partial config or before a full multi-agent list exists, so a setup that intends a custom default agent can still resolve the main session key and default agent directory as `main`.\n\n## Solution\n\nTwo complementary override mechanisms:\n\n### 1. Config key: `agents.defaultAgentId`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaultAgentId\": \"maine-lobster\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Env var: `OPENCLAW_DEFAULT_AGENT_ID`\n\n```bash\nexport OPENCLAW_DEFAULT_AGENT_ID=maine-lobster\n```\n\n### Priority (highest → lowest)\n\n1. `agents.list[].default: true` (explicit default agent)\n2. `agents.list[0]` (first configured agent)\n3. `agents.defaultAgentId` config key\n4. `OPENCLAW_DEFAULT_AGENT_ID` env var\n5. Hardcoded `\"main\"` (backward compatible)\n\n## Changes\n\n- Adds `agents.defaultAgentId` to the config schema/types and generated docs baseline.\n- Updates `resolveDefaultAgentId()`, `listAgentIds()`, `resolveDefaultAgentDir()`, and main-session key resolution to honor config/env fallback values.\n- Keeps populated `agents.list` behavior unchanged: list default/first entry still wins.\n- Updates provider auth/default-agent directory resolution to use the effective default agent.\n- Adds regression tests for config default, env fallback, default dir, and main-session key behavior.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `pnpm config:schema:check`\n- `pnpm config:docs:check`\n- `pnpm test src/agents/agent-scope-config.test.ts src/config/sessions/main-session.test.ts src/config/sessions/session-key.test.ts src/commands/auth-choice.test.ts src/commands/auth-choice.apply.plugin-provider.test.ts --maxWorkers=1`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git merge-tree --write-tree HEAD origin/main` → merge-clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: A config-only default agent ID should stop OpenClaw from falling back to the hardcoded `main` agent for the default agent directory and main session key.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw checkout rebased onto latest `origin/main`, running the patched TypeScript source directly with Node/tsx in `/root/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-pr-acpx/pr-51762`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```console\n$ node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'\nimport { resolveDefaultAgentId, resolveDefaultAgentDir } from './src/agents/agent-scope-config.ts';\nimport { resolveMainSessionKey } from './src/config/sessions/main-session.ts';\nconst cfg = { agents: { defaultAgentId: 'Ops Team' }, session: { mainKey: 'main' } };\nconst env = { OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR: '/tmp/openclaw-real-proof' };\nconsole.log('defaultAgentId=' + resolveDefaultAgentId(cfg, env));\nconsole.log('defaultAgentDir=' + resolveDefaultAgentDir(cfg, env));\nconsole.log('mainSessionKey=' + resolveMainSessionKey(cfg, env));\nEOF\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**: Terminal output copied from the patched real source command above:\n\n```console\ndefaultAgentId=ops-team\ndefaultAgentDir=/tmp/openclaw-real-proof/agents/ops-team/agent\nmainSessionKey=agent:ops-team:main\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: `agents.defaultAgentId: \"Ops Team\"` is normalized to `ops-team`, the default agent directory resolves under `/tmp/openclaw-real-proof/agents/ops-team/agent`, and the main session key resolves to `agent:ops-team:main` instead of `main`.\n- **What was not tested**: No browser/UI flow was tested; this PR changes config/session/agent resolution behavior and was verified through the live runtime resolver functions plus the targeted regression/check suite above.\n\nFixes #17477 🦞\n",
        "branch": "feat/configurable-default-agent-id",
